{{Quote|It's Traut's promise ring. It was on his left hand&mdash;on the arm that you cut off. But how did it end up in my stew?|[[Zak Arranda/Legends|Zak Arranda]] interrogates [[Galt]]|<ref name="Galaxy of Fear: The Hunger">''[[Galaxy of Fear: The Hunger]]''</ref>}}
'''Promise rings''' were worn on the second-to-last finger on the left hand as a symbol of marriage. They were made of numerous metals. The [[Smuggler/Legends|smuggler]] [[Traut]] wore a [[Silver/Legends|silver]] promise ring. While he was on [[Dagobah/Legends|Dagobah]], his arm was amputated by [[The Children]] who used it in a stew. [[Zak Arranda/Legends|Zak Arranda]] realized the cannibalistic nature of the Children when he found Traut's promise ring in his bowl of stew.

